# Tool-generated evidence artifacts — DO NOT COMMIT.
#
# These are deterministically (re)generated by the scripts noted in each file's
# "Machine-generated by …" header. Committing them made every parallel lane that
# runs a gate/audit rewrite the same files → constant merge conflicts (this
# blocked a `git pull` this session). Same anti-pattern the repo already reversed
# for the committed `dependency-graph*.mmd` files (see
# .github/workflows/arch-graph-comment.yml). Regenerate locally on demand:
#   pnpm inventory:operations   # tf-7whh-*
#   pnpm inventory:schemas      # tf-pxxe-*
#   pnpm gate:test-only-exports # tf-uc8u-*
#   pnpm audit:exports          # tf-o7id-*
#
# Hand-written findings (analysis, manifests, removal plans) have no
# "Machine-generated" header and are NOT ignored — they stay committed.
